<div class="page-faq">
  <h1 class="page-faq__title reveal">{{ 'pages.faq.title' | t }}</h1>

  {%- if page.content != blank -%}
    <div class="reveal">{{ page.content }}</div>
  {%- else -%}

    <div class="faq-item reveal">
      <button class="faq-item__btn" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="faq-item__question">How do I know the grade is accurate?</span>
        <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-item__body" role="region">
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Every issue listed as CGC or CBCS graded carries the cert number in the condition
          data table. You can verify the grade directly on the grading authority's website.
          Raw (ungraded) books are photographed extensively and described honestly —
          we note flaws we observe, including minor ones that don't affect our asking price.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item reveal">
      <button class="faq-item__btn" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="faq-item__question">Do you accept returns?</span>
        <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-item__body" role="region">
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Yes, within 7 days of confirmed delivery, for any reason. The book must be
          returned in the same condition as shipped. Return shipping is at the buyer's
          expense unless the book arrived damaged or significantly misrepresented.
          Contact us before shipping anything back.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item reveal">
      <button class="faq-item__btn" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="faq-item__question">How do you ship? Is it insured?</span>
        <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-item__body" role="region">
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          All orders ship fully insured. Slabbed (graded) books are double-boxed with foam
          padding inside a rigid mailer. Raw books are boarded, bagged, and secured inside a
          rigid flat mailer. We ship within 3 business days of purchase. Signature
          confirmation is required on orders over $250.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item reveal">
      <button class="faq-item__btn" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="faq-item__question">What is the Private Client List?</span>
        <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-item__body" role="region">
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          The Private Client List is our early-access email list. Subscribers receive drop
          notifications 12–16 hours before the general public — typically Friday evening for
          a Saturday morning vault opening. There is no fee and no commitment. You simply
          get to shop first.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item reveal">
      <button class="faq-item__btn" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="faq-item__question">How often do you drop?</span>
        <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-item__body" role="region">
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Infrequently, and intentionally so. We don't list books until we're satisfied with
          the curation, the photography, and the write-ups. Most drops are 20–50 issues.
          We will not rush a drop to hit a schedule.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item reveal">
      <button class="faq-item__btn" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="faq-item__question">Do you buy collections?</span>
        <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-item__body" role="region">
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Sometimes. We are selective and slow, so if you need a fast sale, we are
          probably not the right buyer. If you have a significant collection and want a
          thoughtful offer from someone who will read every book, contact us.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item reveal">
      <button class="faq-item__btn" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="faq-item__question">What does "ALLOCATED" mean?</span>
        <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-item__body" role="region">
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Occasionally a book is reserved for a Private Client List member before the
          public vault opens. "ALLOCATED" means the issue has been earmarked for a
          specific buyer but the transaction is not yet complete. If an allocated
          book becomes available, we will update the listing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  {%- endif -%}
</div>

<script>
(function () {
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item__btn').forEach(function (btn) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var item = btn.closest('.faq-item');
      var isOpen = item.classList.contains('is-open');

      // Close all
      document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item.is-open').forEach(function (open) {
        open.classList.remove('is-open');
        open.querySelector('.faq-item__btn').setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
      });

      // Toggle current
      if (!isOpen) {
        item.classList.add('is-open');
        btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
      }
    });
  });
})();
</script>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "FAQ Page",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
